cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a problem related to clustering and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents algorithms and bounds for a new problem. "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper introduces a new unsupervised learning problem and discusses its relation to Support Vector Machines. "cs.CC" (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper proves lower bounds for the problem. "cs.CG" (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with hyperplanes and distances in high-dimensional space. "cs.DM" (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible category as the paper presents a reduction from a particular version of the PCP theorem.
